Solved one of the most challenging problems on LeetCode: **2035. Partition Array Into Two Arrays to Minimize Sum Difference** using Python.

At first, the problem appears to require checking every possible partition, which leads to an exponential-time brute-force solution that is not feasible for the given constraints.

The key was recognizing that this problem can be solved efficiently using the **Meet in the Middle** technique.

### Approach

* Split the array into two equal halves.
* Generate all possible subset sums for each half while keeping track of how many elements are selected in every subset.
* Group the subset sums by the number of selected elements, since the final partition must contain exactly **n** elements.
* Sort the subset sums of one half and use **Binary Search** to efficiently find the combination that brings the selected sum closest to half of the total array sum.
* Calculate the minimum possible difference between the two partition sums by evaluating only the closest candidates.

### Concepts Used

* Meet in the Middle
* Binary Search (`bisect`)
* Bitmasking
* Subset Sum Generation
* Time Complexity Optimization

Problems like this highlight the importance of identifying the right algorithmic technique rather than relying on brute force. Every challenging problem solved is another opportunity to strengthen problem-solving skills and deepen understanding of advanced algorithms.

